OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The maker of popular video game        
OL,6, Fortnite has agreed to pay $520m       
OL,7, (#427m) to resolve claims from US      
OL,8, regulators that it violated child      
OL,9, privacy laws and tricked users into    
OL,10, making purchases.                      
OL,12,FThe Federal Trade Commission (FTC) said
OL,13,Fthe firm duped players with "deceptive 
OL,14,Finterfaces" that could trigger         
OL,15,Fpurchases while the game loaded.       
OL,17,FIt also accused it of using            
OL,18,F"privacy-invasive" default settings.   
OL,20,FEpic Games blamed "past designs".      
